# python-path-resolution-cwd-resolve-contract — History

## v1.1.0 (2026-06-13)

**Changed by:** Issue #1309 plan review — P3/TDD gap finding
**Verification:** unverified

### What changed
- Added new Failed Attempts row: isinstance-only check as regression guard
- Added new When to Use trigger: TDD regression guard planning for path helpers
- Added Results & Parameters example: insufficient vs required assertion
- Added history frontmatter field

### Why
The initial v1.0.0 skill captured the Path.cwd().resolve() fix but omitted the critical
TDD lesson: isinstance(result, Path) alone does not prove the resolved-path contract and
passes both before and after the fix on Linux. The plan reviewer identified this as a
major P3/TDD gap (NOGO grade C). The corrected plan adds assert result.is_absolute()
as the required regression guard.

